It’s a dialogue about love and memory, the unfolding spectrum of gender and sexuality and the ever evolving straits of art. The past has evolved into the present and is budding into a future : more inclusive more equitable more open yet more grounded — Fashion Direction for @officialbyredo

latestPosts.caption:
BLONI at THE MET GALA

Diya Mehta Jatia (@dmjatia ) in custom BLONI at the Met Gala 2025. 

It is a BLONI reimagination of the tailored suit that has gestures of experiment, freedom and history. The suit is structured like a fine thin sheet that rises above the shoulder and extends as a train below like in a gown, all paying homage to the assertive line of tailoring. The suit is custom tailored in pure Himalayan cashmere with fully encrusted and embroidered  back drenched in fifteen thousand white clear quartz, known in Indian metaphysics for its spiritual power of healing and clarity. The Nehru cap brings together an aesthetic of modern freedom, the carved silver cane a symbol of crafted swagger paired with gold and polki diamond jewelry.
